OL,3,CStudy finds women less likely to
OL,4,Creceive CPR from bystanders
OL,6,FWomen are less likely to receive
OL,7,Fbystander CPR than men, according to
OL,8,Fstatistics from St John Ambulance.
OL,10,FThe charity says the reasons behind
OL,11,Fthis may include people worrying about
OL,12,Fhurting or touching women.
OL,14,FTilly Swift, a CPR trainer in , said:
OL,15,F"There is that fear that something is
OL,16,Fgoing to be brought back onto them
OL,17,Fwhen trying to resuscitate a casualty.
