OL,3,CStudy finds women less likely to
OL,4,Creceive CPR from bystanders
OL,6,F"As long as you are keeping that
OL,7,Fperson's dignity ... and just being as
OL,8,Fconcise as possible and stepping
OL,9,Fforward and doing something, that is
OL,10,Ffar better than nothing at all."
OL,12,FSt John Ambulance says that prompt
OL,13,Ffirst aid can increase the chances of
OL,14,Fsurvival by up to 70%.
OL,16,FDaryl Perkins, who works for the
OL,17,Fcharity, said: "Of course people are
OL,18,Fconcerned that somebody touching a
OL,19,Ffemale, maybe having to remove
OL,20,Fclothing, having to expose them, may
OL,21,Fbe very uncomfortable for them.
